DTEND:20260305T085400
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-1.078ft at 06:36\n-2.957ft at 08:54\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Shorter to mid period NW swell mix due to pick up. The shorter period will
  limit size a bit for Santa Cruz\, but it still looks good for fun waist t
 o shoulder high range waves\, showing most size in the afternoon on the eb
 bing tide. There will also be a little underlying S Southern Hemi pulse he
 lping then.\n\nLight northerly wind is currently expected in the morning\,
  becoming moderate NW for the afternoon. Conditions in town should stay cl
 ean or at least semi clean all day. 
END:VEVENT
